I"\<p>Screen time has exploded during COVID-19. Children are moving less and staring at screens more (for both school and leisure). From this <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7190470/pdf/main.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">study</a>, here is data on Chinese adolescents:<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"></figure></p>

<p><img loading="lazy" width="507" height="333" src="https://i2.wp.com/mattmetzgar.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image.png?resize=507%2C333&#038;ssl=1" /></p>

<p>Simply put, most children are not getting sufficient physical activity every day.</p>

<p>Limiting screen time <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30199286/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">leads</a> to increased physical activity.</p>

<p>Screen time limits can improve overall health for both children and adults.</p>
